      "target": {
        "kind": "pull_request",
        "title": "fix(cli): add IPv4 loopback host to isPortBusy",
        "body": "Fixes #94426\n\n## Summary\n\n`isPortBusy` preflight in `startSshPortForward` missed IPv4-only occupants on dual-stack hosts because the default probe binds the IPv6 wildcard (::), which does not conflict with IPv4-only listeners.\n\n## Root Cause\n\n`tryListenOnPort({ port, exclusive: true })` without a `host` parameter binds the default address (:: on IPv6-enabled systems). An IPv4-only listener on 127.0.0.1 does not conflict with ::, so `isPortBusy` returns `false` for a busy port.\n\n## Changes\n\n- `src/cli/ports.ts`: Pass `host: \"127.0.0.1\"` to `tryListenOnPort`\n\n## Real behavior proof\n\n**Behavior addressed**: IPv4-only port occupants are now correctly detected on dual-stack hosts.\n\n**Evidence after fix**:\n\n```text\n$ npx tsx -e '...'\n=== Test 1: IPv4 server, probe with ::1 (old default on IPv6-first) ===\n  Result: FREE  ❌ - bug! IPv6 probe misses IPv4 occupant\n  Result: BUSY  ✅ - fix: IPv4 probe detects IPv4 occupant\n\n=== Test 2: IPv6 server, probe with 127.0.0.1 (reverse case) ===\n  Result: FREE  ✅ - expected, IPv4 probe misses IPv6-only occupant (correct)\n```\n\nTest 1 confirms the bug: an IPv4-only listener is invisible to a host-less (IPv6-first) probe. With `host: \"127.0.0.1\"`, the probe correctly detects the occupant. Test 2 confirms no false positive for IPv6-only listeners.\n\n**What was not tested**: End-to-end `gateway --force` on a dual-stack host (requires a running gateway).\n\n## Risk\n\n- [x] Backwards compatible (single-host argument addition)\n- [x] No false positive for IPv6-only occupants\n\nCloses: #94426",
